definitions: produce more of (something) than is wanted or needed

examples.text: our unplanned manufacturing system continually overproduces consumer products

shortDefinitions: produce more of something than is wanted or needed

definitions: record or arrange (a song or piece of music) in such an elaborate way that the spontaneity or artistry of the original material is lost

examples.text: he has shown a disturbing tendency to overproduce songs

shortDefinitions: record or arrange song in overly elaborate way
